- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically coreference resolution. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new model for selectional preferences which is a key aspect of AI systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed model is an embedding model which is a common technique in machine learning. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks for coreference resolution. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as coreference resolution is a task that can be applied to information retrieval systems.
